quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  4,116,"Verily Allah shall not forgive that aught be associated with Him, and He will forgive all else unto whomsoever He liketh; and whosoever associateth ought with Allah, hath surely strayed away a far straying"
  4,117,"They invoke beside Him but females, and they invoke not but a Satan rebellious"
  4,118,"Allah hath accursed him. And he said: surely shall take of Thine bondmen a portion allotted"
  4,119,"And surely I will lead them and will fill them with vain desires, and I will command them so that they will slit the ears of the cattle, and I will command them so that they will alter the creation of Allah. And whosoever taketh Satan for a patron, instead of Allah, shall surely suffer a manifest loss"
  4,120,The Satan maketh them promises and filleth them with vain desires. and Satan promiseth them not but delusion
  4,121,"These: their resort shall be Hell, and they shall not find therefrom an escape"
  4,122,"And those who believe and work righteous works, anon We shall make them enter Gardens whereunder the rivers flow, as abiders therein for ever: promise of Allah, true. And who is more truthful than Allah in speech"
  4,123,"Not by your vain desires nor by the vain desires of the people of the Book; whosoever worketh an evil, shall be requited therewith, and he will not find beside Allah a patron nor a helper"
  4,124,"And whosoever worketh of righteous works, male or female, and is a believer, these shall enter the Garden and shall not be wronged a speck"
  4,125,"And who can be better in religion than he who submitteth his countenance unto Allah, and sincere, and followeth the faith of Ibrahim, the upright And Allah took Ibrahim for a friend"
  4,126,And Allah's is whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is in the earth; and of everything Allah is ever an Encompasser